The paper discusses the effectiveness of Google Scholar in searching for gray literature, which is often not formally published or indexed in traditional databases. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography (cs.CR), and possibly cybernetics (cs.CY) as well. However, given the focus on search strategies and information retrieval, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories.
